WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.251 --> 00:00:03.045
[laughs]

2
00:00:03.128 --> 00:00:04.772
[Queen Kane] <i>Let's make a pact. right now.</i>

3
00:00:04.796 --> 00:00:08.175
<i>I will never lie to you.
You will never lie to me.</i>

4
00:00:08.258 --> 00:00:09.593
Agreed.

5
00:00:09.676 --> 00:00:13.138
[Watts] Lord Harlan. we made
no secret of beheading your brother.

6
00:00:13.222 --> 00:00:15.474
We sent his head back to you
as a courtesy.

7
00:00:18.185 --> 00:00:19.895
[grunts. strains]

8
00:00:19.978 --> 00:00:22.373
- [Maghra] Ambassador. I apologize.
- This conference was a waste of time.

9
00:00:22.397 --> 00:00:23.941
- We are done here.
- [Harlan] Oh.

10
00:00:27.152 --> 00:00:28.403
- [slashes]
- [grunts]

11
00:00:28.487 --> 00:00:29.988
Help! We've been betrayed.

12
00:00:30.072 --> 00:00:31.156
[screams. gurgles]

13
00:00:31.240 --> 00:00:32.698
[Haniwa grunts]

14
00:00:33.325 --> 00:00:34.535
You did this.

15
00:00:34.618 --> 00:00:37.162
Wren. No.

16
00:00:37.246 --> 00:00:38.997
[cries] You used me.

17
00:00:39.081 --> 00:00:40.958
[Maghra] This assassin has Payan markings.

18
00:00:41.625 --> 00:00:42.668
Sibeth.

19
00:00:42.751 --> 00:00:46.421
This whole summit was just a way
for her to wage a war we couldn't stop.

20
00:00:47.214 --> 00:00:48.715
[Wren] <i>The attack…</i>

21
00:00:48.799 --> 00:00:50.384
<i>I believe it was led by Baba Voss.</i>

22
00:00:50.467 --> 00:00:51.627
- [guard strains]
- [grunting]

23
00:00:51.677 --> 00:00:56.014
[Edo Voss] Queen Kane wanted war?
No. I'm not surprised.

24
00:00:56.807 --> 00:00:58.308
[Maghra] <i>Within a very short time…</i>

25
00:00:58.392 --> 00:00:59.392
How was your trip?

26
00:01:01.520 --> 00:01:03.522
…my sister will no longer be queen.

27
00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:11.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

28
00:01:13.130 --> 00:01:17.467
Talk of peace is in the past now.

29
00:01:20.137 --> 00:01:23.098
After the delegation's failure
at the peace summit.

30
00:01:23.182 --> 00:01:26.143
we're left with only one path forward.

31
00:01:27.269 --> 00:01:28.270
War.

32
00:01:30.314 --> 00:01:32.608
Remember this moment.

33
00:01:32.691 --> 00:01:35.652
Your names will be burned
into Payan history

34
00:01:35.736 --> 00:01:39.031
as the women and men
who stood with their queen

35
00:01:39.114 --> 00:01:42.951
to lead Paya into a new and blessed age.

36
00:01:43.035 --> 00:01:45.871
She's lying. Someone needs to stop her.

37
00:01:47.206 --> 00:01:48.207
Not now.

38
00:01:48.290 --> 00:01:51.210
Lord Harlan.
have all the representatives signed?

39
00:01:54.588 --> 00:01:55.589
Yes.

40
00:01:56.256 --> 00:01:59.218
The knots of all the representatives
have been added.

41
00:02:00.135 --> 00:02:03.222
[Queen Kane] Then. my ladies and lords.

42
00:02:03.305 --> 00:02:05.766
- we're now at war.
- [murmuring]

43
00:02:05.849 --> 00:02:07.976
Have your captains report
to my Witchfinder general

44
00:02:08.060 --> 00:02:09.186
for assignments immediately.

45
00:02:09.269 --> 00:02:12.397
There is still another matter
to be brought before this council.

46
00:02:13.774 --> 00:02:17.945
Princess Maghra. there is always something
with you. isn't there? What is it now?

47
00:02:18.028 --> 00:02:19.488
It's about the Witchfinders.

48
00:02:20.781 --> 00:02:21.949
What about them?

49
00:02:22.991 --> 00:02:24.910
They will not fight for you.

50
00:02:27.412 --> 00:02:31.458
My Witchfinders will do as I say.
as they have done my entire reign.

51
00:02:31.542 --> 00:02:33.502
They're my army.

52
00:02:33.585 --> 00:02:34.711
[Tamacti Jun] No.

53
00:02:34.795 --> 00:02:36.797
[footsteps approaching]

54
00:02:44.263 --> 00:02:46.723
They are my army.

55
00:02:48.308 --> 00:02:49.518
Tamacti Jun?

56
00:02:50.102 --> 00:02:52.604
I'm glad you haven't forgotten me.

57
00:02:52.688 --> 00:02:55.983
[Queen Kane] You're alive!
Thank the God Flame.

58
00:02:56.066 --> 00:02:58.902
- You have no idea what I went through.
- [thumps]

59
00:02:58.986 --> 00:03:03.490
If you're gonna trade in lies. make sure
the truth is buried with the dead.

60
00:03:03.574 --> 00:03:08.120
- Lies?
- It was you who destroyed Kanzua.

61
00:03:08.203 --> 00:03:10.455
[court clamoring]

62
00:03:10.539 --> 00:03:11.665
He is lying!

63
00:03:12.749 --> 00:03:14.041
Arrest this man.

64
00:03:15.794 --> 00:03:17.796
I said arrest this man!

65
00:03:17.880 --> 00:03:20.841
They don't serve you anymore.

66
00:03:22.134 --> 00:03:24.219
- Tak!
- [warriors] Tak! Tak!

67
00:03:24.303 --> 00:03:26.096
Tak! Tak! Tak! Tak!

68
00:03:26.180 --> 00:03:30.475
Tak! Tak! Tak! Tak! Tak! Tak! Tak! Tak!

69
00:03:30.559 --> 00:03:35.147
It was you who murdered your own people…

70
00:03:36.773 --> 00:03:39.067
who killed their families.

71
00:03:41.278 --> 00:03:43.488
My family.

72
00:03:48.952 --> 00:03:54.541
It was you who tried to murder me.

73
00:03:57.252 --> 00:03:59.755
These are serious allegations. General.

74
00:03:59.838 --> 00:04:02.466
They're not allegations. They're truths.

75
00:04:04.009 --> 00:04:05.677
Like you. Captain Gosset.

76
00:04:06.512 --> 00:04:09.223
I have been loyal to the crown
my entire life.

77
00:04:10.098 --> 00:04:11.308
But this queen…

78
00:04:12.684 --> 00:04:13.852
this woman…

79
00:04:15.103 --> 00:04:17.648
this thing

80
00:04:17.731 --> 00:04:19.191
- is an abomination.
- [gasps]

81
00:04:19.274 --> 00:04:20.859
He keeps on lying!

82
00:04:20.943 --> 00:04:23.403
Maghra. tell them he's lying.

83
00:04:24.279 --> 00:04:25.697
He speaks the truth.

84
00:04:26.865 --> 00:04:29.159
You've betrayed your people
for the last time.

85
00:04:30.536 --> 00:04:33.372
This council has a decision to make.

86
00:04:34.456 --> 00:04:36.875
War is now inevitable.

87
00:04:38.377 --> 00:04:42.297
But will we be led by this lying murderer…

88
00:04:43.423 --> 00:04:49.137
or will we fight for the true queen…

89
00:04:50.138 --> 00:04:51.557
Maghra?

90
00:04:53.267 --> 00:04:57.271
Oh. so it's a coup?

91
00:04:57.813 --> 00:04:59.231
I understand.

92
00:05:00.065 --> 00:05:02.192
At our nation's gravest hour.

93
00:05:02.276 --> 00:05:06.822
my sister resorts to trickery
and lies to steal the throne.

94
00:05:06.905 --> 00:05:12.911
But she forgets that my army
is much larger than a few Witchfinders.

95
00:05:13.745 --> 00:05:17.040
Captain Gosset. arrest these traitors.

96
00:05:18.041 --> 00:05:19.251
Yeah…

97
00:05:20.752 --> 00:05:21.753
No.

98
00:05:23.671 --> 00:05:27.467
The army of Pennsa stands
with Queen Maghra.

99
00:05:27.551 --> 00:05:30.429
She's not your fucking queen!

100
00:05:30.512 --> 00:05:32.681
Let's agree to disagree. shall we?

101
00:05:33.849 --> 00:05:37.227
I can confirm the allegations
made by Tamacti Jun are true.

102
00:05:37.311 --> 00:05:39.813
I have witnesses from Kanzua
who will tell you

103
00:05:39.897 --> 00:05:42.941
the destruction of the city was her doing.

104
00:05:43.025 --> 00:05:44.776
[court murmuring]

105
00:05:44.860 --> 00:05:46.403
[Tamacti Jun] And queen or no.

106
00:05:46.486 --> 00:05:49.656
treason and murder
are punishable by death.

107
00:05:49.740 --> 00:05:53.744
Wait. wait. wait. Wait.
I'm entitled to a trial.

108
00:05:54.328 --> 00:05:58.957
You yourself just declared the war
you so desperately wanted.

109
00:06:00.542 --> 00:06:05.130
And by knotting the war declaration.

110
00:06:06.215 --> 00:06:10.010
you transferred authority from the courts…

111
00:06:11.970 --> 00:06:13.222
to the generals.

112
00:06:13.305 --> 00:06:14.389
[gasps]

113
00:06:15.557 --> 00:06:16.850
[breathes shakily]

114
00:06:16.934 --> 00:06:18.435
You thought this through.

115
00:06:19.978 --> 00:06:21.396
I've had some time.

116
00:06:23.941 --> 00:06:26.777
- [breathes shakily]
- Thank you for your service.

117
00:06:29.029 --> 00:06:30.155
Wait!

118
00:06:31.073 --> 00:06:32.699
She is with child.

119
00:06:34.451 --> 00:06:36.370
[court murmuring]

120
00:06:36.453 --> 00:06:40.999
Sibeth lost her child
shortly after we arrived in Pennsa.

121
00:06:41.625 --> 00:06:43.001
This is a new one.

122
00:06:43.961 --> 00:06:45.420
Still forming.

123
00:06:46.505 --> 00:06:48.882
I feel him strongly.

124
00:06:49.758 --> 00:06:53.554
This child must not be killed
for the sins of the mother.

125
00:06:55.639 --> 00:06:57.683
Her death can wait. Toad.

126
00:06:57.766 --> 00:07:00.227
That's twice now you failed to kill me.
Tamacti Jun.

127
00:07:00.310 --> 00:07:02.729
- Get her out of here.
- The prophecy remains!

128
00:07:02.813 --> 00:07:05.274
[breathes heavily]
And the God Flame is still with me.

129
00:07:05.357 --> 00:07:08.527
The child has arrived just in time
to save his mother.

130
00:07:09.111 --> 00:07:12.072
People. be true to the crown!

131
00:07:12.155 --> 00:07:15.284
Do not rest until your queen is back
on the throne.

132
00:07:15.367 --> 00:07:17.828
And the rest of you traitors.
you will be flayed alive.

133
00:07:17.911 --> 00:07:20.038
Put her in her chambers under guard.

134
00:07:20.622 --> 00:07:23.250
[sighs]
Keeping her in the palace is unwise.

135
00:07:23.333 --> 00:07:26.086
[Maghra] It is the most fortified building
in all of Pennsa.

136
00:07:26.170 --> 00:07:27.880
[horn blowing]

137
00:07:28.839 --> 00:07:29.840
Quiet.

138
00:07:32.759 --> 00:07:33.969
Do you hear that?

139
00:07:34.052 --> 00:07:38.473
[horn continues]

140
00:07:39.933 --> 00:07:41.476
Woodvale has fallen.

141
00:07:49.318 --> 00:07:53.030
[Edo Voss] We took Woodvale
with zero Trivantian casualties.

142
00:07:54.281 --> 00:07:57.451
Thanks to your vision. we arrived
days before they were expecting us.

143
00:07:57.534 --> 00:08:00.287
Still managed
to get the signal out though.

144
00:08:00.370 --> 00:08:02.498
Pennsa knows we're on our way.

145
00:08:02.581 --> 00:08:05.461
That won't make them any more ready
for the full might of this battalion.

146
00:08:06.835 --> 00:08:09.046
And once the council
hears of our fast victory…

147
00:08:10.214 --> 00:08:12.299
they will finally ratify my strategy.

148
00:08:13.383 --> 00:08:16.053
You mean using sighted soldiers?

149
00:08:21.016 --> 00:08:25.938
General. please.
the council cannot know about me.

150
00:08:27.397 --> 00:08:29.525
I won't identify you until it's safe.

151
00:08:30.442 --> 00:08:33.737
Wren. you're like a daughter to me.

152
00:08:34.446 --> 00:08:37.032
I will protect you. You have my word.

153
00:10:07.164 --> 00:10:09.750
The Trivantians have reached Woodvale
faster than expected.

154
00:10:09.833 --> 00:10:14.087
At this rate. they'll be in Pennsa
in five or six days.

155
00:10:14.171 --> 00:10:16.882
How could their army be moving this fast?

156
00:10:16.965 --> 00:10:19.301
They have sighted soldiers
guiding their armies.

157
00:10:19.384 --> 00:10:22.471
The Trivantians wouldn't condone sight
in any form.

158
00:10:22.554 --> 00:10:26.016
[Haniwa] The commander general has been
secretly recruiting and training them.

159
00:10:26.099 --> 00:10:28.727
If the Trivantians reach Pennsa.
we're finished.

160
00:10:28.810 --> 00:10:34.024
Agreed. Greenhill Gap.
Is the fortress still active?

161
00:10:34.107 --> 00:10:36.026
Of course. Fully fortified. 20 men.

162
00:10:36.109 --> 00:10:37.444
We'll make our stand there.

163
00:10:37.528 --> 00:10:40.948
No. Greenhill Gap's a stone's throw
from Pennsa. It's too close.

164
00:10:41.031 --> 00:10:43.635
[Tamacti Jun] It's the only place
that we can command the high ground.

165
00:10:43.659 --> 00:10:44.660
Gives us a chance.

166
00:10:45.327 --> 00:10:47.454
Any word on their numbers?

167
00:10:47.538 --> 00:10:49.623
They're heavily committed in the west.

168
00:10:49.706 --> 00:10:53.377
Our spies estimate 250 men.
A small force by Trivantian standards.

169
00:10:53.460 --> 00:10:55.170
Bigger than ours.

170
00:10:55.921 --> 00:10:58.757
I want every available soldier
and munition in Paya

171
00:10:58.841 --> 00:11:01.426
at Greenhill Gap in two days' time.

172
00:11:02.094 --> 00:11:03.637
Captain Gosset. ready your soldiers.

173
00:11:03.720 --> 00:11:05.889
We march tomorrow
with the rise of the God Flame.

174
00:11:05.973 --> 00:11:08.016
No. Think. Maghra.

175
00:11:08.100 --> 00:11:11.144
If they truly have sighted soldiers.
we're at even more of a disadvantage.

176
00:11:11.228 --> 00:11:13.105
You will have sighted soldiers too.

177
00:11:14.022 --> 00:11:15.482
- No.
- We're going.

178
00:11:16.483 --> 00:11:17.860
You are not soldiers.

179
00:11:18.485 --> 00:11:21.196
No. we're the children of the queen.
This is our fight too.

180
00:11:21.280 --> 00:11:24.324
Your father is right.
You and your sister have no training.

181
00:11:24.408 --> 00:11:27.202
You cannot be expected to fight
just because you can see.

182
00:11:27.995 --> 00:11:31.248
- I don't wanna intrude on family matters...
- Then do not.

183
00:11:31.331 --> 00:11:35.919
But as you yourself have said many times.
we face a far superior army.

184
00:11:38.088 --> 00:11:40.883
We need every advantage
we can get in this battle.

185
00:11:40.966 --> 00:11:43.468
[Baba Voss] Sight offers no advantage
on the killing field.

186
00:11:44.011 --> 00:11:45.721
As I have learned with my own children.

187
00:11:45.804 --> 00:11:47.723
more often than not.
their vision betrays them.

188
00:11:47.806 --> 00:11:52.603
And these sighted soldiers will give
Edo's army a false confidence.

189
00:11:52.686 --> 00:11:54.271
We need not do the same with ours.

190
00:11:54.354 --> 00:11:56.398
Edo has developed systems for using them.

191
00:11:57.065 --> 00:11:58.734
I've witnessed it myself.

192
00:11:59.985 --> 00:12:01.778
Papa. you are a great warrior…

193
00:12:03.238 --> 00:12:06.033
but the truth is
there are things we can do that you can't.

194
00:12:06.116 --> 00:12:09.995
That is the same thing that Jerlamarel
said just before I took his eyes.

195
00:12:10.078 --> 00:12:11.121
[scoffs]

196
00:12:11.205 --> 00:12:13.207
[Kofun]
You can't protect us from this fight.

197
00:12:13.290 --> 00:12:14.583
It is not a fight.

198
00:12:14.666 --> 00:12:17.544
This is a slaughter.
and my children will not be a part of it!

199
00:12:17.628 --> 00:12:19.296
- Yes. I will.
- I will.

200
00:12:19.379 --> 00:12:21.048
[Baba Voss sighs]

201
00:12:21.131 --> 00:12:22.132
Maghra.

202
00:12:24.635 --> 00:12:27.888
- We are not sending our children to war.
- I can't stop them.

203
00:12:27.971 --> 00:12:30.611
You said you became queen to protect them.
And this is what you do?

204
00:12:30.641 --> 00:12:33.185
Do you think it's any easier for me
to let them go?

205
00:12:33.268 --> 00:12:36.021
Believe me. I would like nothing more
than just to lock them up.

206
00:12:36.104 --> 00:12:38.440
Then do that. We will force them to stay.

207
00:12:39.274 --> 00:12:42.069
Haniwa and Kofun are not children anymore.

208
00:12:42.152 --> 00:12:45.822
They're adults
with opinions and ideas of their own.

209
00:12:45.906 --> 00:12:46.990
[Baba Voss groans]

210
00:12:48.992 --> 00:12:51.245
[Baba Voss sighs]

211
00:12:51.328 --> 00:12:53.080
It was not so long ago

212
00:12:53.163 --> 00:12:57.584
that our entire world
was just the four of us.

213
00:12:57.668 --> 00:12:59.711
We never needed any of this.

214
00:13:00.587 --> 00:13:02.214
When we were all separated.

215
00:13:03.006 --> 00:13:05.467
you must have thought
you would never get your family back.

216
00:13:05.968 --> 00:13:07.386
And now you have.

217
00:13:09.096 --> 00:13:10.764
Let us take our children.

218
00:13:10.848 --> 00:13:13.559
Let us be a family again.
This is not our fight.

219
00:13:13.642 --> 00:13:15.811
Please just... just stop saying that.

220
00:13:15.894 --> 00:13:17.855
This is a war that was started
by your sister!

221
00:13:17.938 --> 00:13:20.524
No. We've all made choices
that brought us here today.

222
00:13:20.607 --> 00:13:24.027
Now war is upon us.
and we must greet it head-on.

223
00:13:28.532 --> 00:13:31.785
You speak of war as if you've been in one.

224
00:13:31.869 --> 00:13:34.955
You have no idea
what you are sending our children into.

225
00:13:35.038 --> 00:13:37.875
- I am not sending them in...
- Their deaths will be on your hands!

226
00:13:37.958 --> 00:13:39.042
[grunts]

227
00:13:40.127 --> 00:13:42.087
[groans]

228
00:13:45.549 --> 00:13:46.550
[sighs]

229
00:13:58.187 --> 00:14:02.983
I did everything I could
to avoid this war.

230
00:14:04.818 --> 00:14:08.071
But now I have no choice but to win it.

231
00:14:17.122 --> 00:14:19.541
[sighs]

232
00:14:32.095 --> 00:14:33.305
You can't.

233
00:14:40.354 --> 00:14:41.563
Where are you going?

234
00:14:45.400 --> 00:14:46.693
[sighs]

235
00:14:46.777 --> 00:14:50.405
I'm going to war.
Along with the rest of your family.

236
00:15:00.541 --> 00:15:01.583
Do you wanna count it?

237
00:15:02.209 --> 00:15:03.961
You've never been short before.

238
00:15:05.254 --> 00:15:07.256
And you've never failed to deliver.

239
00:15:09.174 --> 00:15:12.010
Once I take payment.
the contract is sealed.

240
00:15:12.094 --> 00:15:13.345
Say you hear.

241
00:15:14.304 --> 00:15:16.515
Must we go through this every time?

242
00:15:17.224 --> 00:15:18.642
Say you hear.

243
00:15:18.725 --> 00:15:20.143
I hear.

244
00:15:20.227 --> 00:15:24.022
The contract cannot be nullified.
Say you hear.

245
00:15:24.106 --> 00:15:26.233
[sighs] I hear.

246
00:15:27.150 --> 00:15:28.777
Now get it done.

247
00:15:28.861 --> 00:15:29.987
Mmm.

248
00:15:38.287 --> 00:15:40.539
Instead of lurking around.
why don't you join me?

249
00:15:44.751 --> 00:15:48.797
The man who just left. who was he?

250
00:15:51.675 --> 00:15:53.468
Pray you never have to find out.

251
00:16:14.615 --> 00:16:15.949
[groans]

252
00:16:33.842 --> 00:16:34.885
Baba?

253
00:16:49.149 --> 00:16:52.569
[snoring]

254
00:17:09.628 --> 00:17:12.256
[snoring continues]

255
00:17:37.281 --> 00:17:38.866
I know you're there.

256
00:17:41.076 --> 00:17:45.998
You've been inside of me. Kofun.
I recognize your scent in my sleep.

257
00:17:49.126 --> 00:17:50.752
Why do you seem happy?

258
00:17:51.670 --> 00:17:53.213
Why wouldn't I be?

259
00:17:54.339 --> 00:17:57.134
My faith has been restored.

260
00:17:57.217 --> 00:17:59.386
The prophecy remains intact.

261
00:18:00.470 --> 00:18:03.640
Do you understand? You're a sacred
instrument of the God Flame.

262
00:18:07.895 --> 00:18:10.022
The baby… [swallows]

263
00:18:11.022 --> 00:18:12.232
…is it mine?

264
00:18:14.151 --> 00:18:15.735
[chuckles]

265
00:18:16.945 --> 00:18:18.780
You know… [chuckles]

266
00:18:20.449 --> 00:18:22.658
[breathes shakily]

267
00:18:23.535 --> 00:18:26.246
- The way every father knows.
- No. You used me.

268
00:18:26.329 --> 00:18:29.333
[chuckles] I don't recall you complaining.

269
00:18:29.916 --> 00:18:32.127
- [grunts] No.
- Mmm. [inhales deeply]

270
00:18:32.211 --> 00:18:33.837
- Stop!
- [grunts]

271
00:18:34.630 --> 00:18:35.714
[sighs]

272
00:18:37.174 --> 00:18:39.968
[breathing heavily]

273
00:18:50.312 --> 00:18:51.438
What are you doing?

274
00:18:53.815 --> 00:18:54.858
What is this?

275
00:18:57.569 --> 00:19:00.030
- [grunts]
- [breathing heavily]

276
00:19:00.113 --> 00:19:01.365
Stop it right now.

277
00:19:02.783 --> 00:19:03.951
If you want to.

278
00:19:05.327 --> 00:19:06.703
[Queen Kane grunts]

279
00:19:09.164 --> 00:19:10.749
You can put an end to your nightmare.

280
00:19:10.833 --> 00:19:12.960
[Kofun breathing heavily]

281
00:19:15.504 --> 00:19:17.005
[Queen Kane grunts]

282
00:19:19.800 --> 00:19:22.386
[choking]

283
00:19:22.469 --> 00:19:23.595
[Kofun pants]

284
00:19:24.346 --> 00:19:25.472
[choking continues]

285
00:19:30.561 --> 00:19:32.729
- [grunts]
- [coughing. straining]

286
00:19:32.813 --> 00:19:35.023
[breathing heavily]

287
00:19:37.442 --> 00:19:39.111
[coughs. groans]

288
00:19:48.996 --> 00:19:49.997
[sighs]

289
00:20:00.591 --> 00:20:02.718
Promised you I'd never lie to you. Kofun.

290
00:20:03.677 --> 00:20:05.179
So I'm gonna tell you the truth.

291
00:20:07.764 --> 00:20:10.309
You still see yourself as a child…

292
00:20:11.977 --> 00:20:13.812
which makes you a weak man.

293
00:20:16.064 --> 00:20:17.900
The time has come for you to be strong.

294
00:20:19.443 --> 00:20:22.905
This child is your son.
and you'll have to claim him as such.

295
00:20:24.573 --> 00:20:27.868
Regardless of whatever immature shame
you might feel in doing so.

296
00:20:27.951 --> 00:20:30.746
not just because he's your son.
but because he's mine.

297
00:20:33.290 --> 00:20:37.336
This child is vital to the future of Paya.

298
00:20:37.419 --> 00:20:40.172
- What are you talking about?
- I tried to explain it to Jerlamarel.

299
00:20:40.255 --> 00:20:43.634
but he thought his vision meant
he didn't need anyone else.

300
00:20:43.717 --> 00:20:46.470
He could just run off.
start his own world.

301
00:20:48.555 --> 00:20:50.974
This world still belongs to the unsighted.

302
00:20:52.851 --> 00:20:57.439
Only I. a queen ordained by God.
can lift it out of darkness

303
00:20:57.523 --> 00:20:59.775
toward a new future governed by light.

304
00:20:59.858 --> 00:21:01.109
You're not queen anymore.

305
00:21:01.985 --> 00:21:03.570
Of course I am.

306
00:21:03.654 --> 00:21:06.114
It'll all be sorted. It's God's will.

307
00:21:06.698 --> 00:21:09.493
Was it God's will for you
to murder the people of Kanzua?

308
00:21:10.077 --> 00:21:12.621
Destroying Kanzua brought me here.

309
00:21:12.704 --> 00:21:14.665
To you. To our baby.

310
00:21:15.249 --> 00:21:16.959
[grunts. breathes heavily]

311
00:21:17.042 --> 00:21:19.753
They are going to kill you
the moment it's born.

312
00:21:19.837 --> 00:21:20.838
[grunts]

313
00:21:20.921 --> 00:21:23.173
Your baby will be an orphan.

314
00:21:24.424 --> 00:21:28.428
No. He's the son of a prince. [chuckles]

315
00:21:29.304 --> 00:21:32.182
I'm nobody's father. [breathes heavily]

316
00:21:32.266 --> 00:21:33.934
[exhales sharply. gasps]

317
00:21:34.017 --> 00:21:36.854
If you abandon him.
you're no different than Jerlamarel.

318
00:21:36.937 --> 00:21:37.938
[grunts]

319
00:21:38.605 --> 00:21:40.357
Tell them the truth. Kofun.

320
00:21:41.316 --> 00:21:43.569
- He's your blood.
- [breathing heavily]

321
00:21:43.652 --> 00:21:46.238
If you die in battle.
the truth will die with you.

322
00:21:47.573 --> 00:21:48.574
Tell them!

323
00:21:49.700 --> 00:21:52.077
Be a fucking man!

324
00:21:53.203 --> 00:21:54.663
[Tamacti Jun] Your Majesty.

325
00:21:56.165 --> 00:21:59.877
I heard a rumor that the queen herself
was girding for battle.

326
00:22:00.836 --> 00:22:02.754
And you think you should stop me?

327
00:22:02.838 --> 00:22:04.923
Oh. I'm not thinking of you at all.

328
00:22:05.007 --> 00:22:08.093
I'm thinking of the soldiers
who will die trying to protect you.

329
00:22:08.760 --> 00:22:10.470
Well. no one need protect me.

330
00:22:10.554 --> 00:22:13.974
There's little purpose in the queen coming
if she doesn't make it known she's coming.

331
00:22:14.057 --> 00:22:17.269
And once she makes it known.
her army will be more focused

332
00:22:17.352 --> 00:22:19.021
on her safety than victory.

333
00:22:19.104 --> 00:22:20.689
She will be a liability.

334
00:22:21.899 --> 00:22:23.775
Do you understand
what you're asking of me?

335
00:22:23.859 --> 00:22:25.319
I'm not asking.

336
00:22:26.612 --> 00:22:28.405
I'm not my sister.

337
00:22:28.488 --> 00:22:31.158
I will not send my people.
my family. into battle

338
00:22:31.241 --> 00:22:33.994
while I sit at home. drinking tea.

339
00:22:34.077 --> 00:22:37.080
That's the reaction of a mother.
not a queen.

340
00:22:37.998 --> 00:22:41.126
Sentimental. not practical.

341
00:22:43.962 --> 00:22:46.173
My job is to win this battle.

342
00:22:46.256 --> 00:22:49.051
And I will not have
my battle plan compromised.

343
00:22:49.134 --> 00:22:50.552
Not even by you.

344
00:22:51.470 --> 00:22:52.679
[Maghra] Sentimental?

345
00:22:54.431 --> 00:22:56.517
So what do you propose I do?

346
00:22:58.060 --> 00:22:59.269
You will do…

347
00:23:00.395 --> 00:23:02.439
what every great leader must do.

348
00:23:04.441 --> 00:23:07.194
Bless and inspire your army.

349
00:23:08.487 --> 00:23:11.198
And be there to pick up the pieces
when we return.

350
00:23:13.116 --> 00:23:14.243
You're serious.

351
00:23:15.327 --> 00:23:17.329
Have you ever known me to be otherwise?

352
00:23:28.173 --> 00:23:29.842
[clicking tongue]

353
00:23:36.431 --> 00:23:38.058
- [clicking tongue]
- [clatters]

354
00:23:43.981 --> 00:23:47.234
[rattling]

355
00:23:51.864 --> 00:23:53.365
[clicking tongue]

356
00:24:01.832 --> 00:24:03.584
[sniffing]

357
00:24:04.168 --> 00:24:06.003
[blade scraping]

358
00:24:19.433 --> 00:24:21.852
I understand you'll be joining us.

359
00:24:29.151 --> 00:24:30.319
[sighs]

360
00:24:34.239 --> 00:24:38.243
It doesn't sound like ordinary God bone.
May I?

361
00:24:44.500 --> 00:24:45.501
Heavy.

362
00:24:46.418 --> 00:24:47.669
Unwieldy.

363
00:24:49.546 --> 00:24:51.215
For a small hand. yes.

364
00:24:56.261 --> 00:24:57.971
A surreal set of alliances.

365
00:24:59.056 --> 00:25:03.519
You are fighting with your former enemy
against your former home.

366
00:25:04.311 --> 00:25:07.064
I fight for my family. not the crown.

367
00:25:07.147 --> 00:25:10.692
Your wife is the crown.
So is there any difference?

368
00:25:13.946 --> 00:25:15.155
I understand.

369
00:25:17.616 --> 00:25:21.161
I once was a husband.

370
00:25:22.120 --> 00:25:23.247
And a father.

371
00:25:27.626 --> 00:25:28.627
Kanzua.

372
00:25:29.628 --> 00:25:32.047
Yes. Kanzua.

373
00:25:34.424 --> 00:25:36.051
[sighs]

374
00:25:38.178 --> 00:25:39.596
Sorry for your loss.

375
00:25:41.265 --> 00:25:44.726
You spent years
fighting in the service of your family.

376
00:25:46.562 --> 00:25:49.690
And I lost my family
in the service of the fight.

377
00:25:53.151 --> 00:25:55.362
I do hope yours fares better than mine.

378
00:26:00.325 --> 00:26:03.203
My own brother
stands between us and victory.

379
00:26:04.830 --> 00:26:07.708
No matter the outcome. I will lose.

380
00:26:09.835 --> 00:26:12.254
If there's a better definition of war…

381
00:26:13.797 --> 00:26:15.507
I have yet to hear it.

382
00:26:16.550 --> 00:26:17.885
You know we can't win.

383
00:26:19.386 --> 00:26:22.264
They are better trained.
They are better armed.

384
00:26:25.100 --> 00:26:26.935
At least there's fewer of us.

385
00:26:30.397 --> 00:26:31.815
[chuckles]

386
00:26:34.902 --> 00:26:36.695
You and I are soldiers.

387
00:26:37.821 --> 00:26:40.365
We fight even when we know
we're gonna lose.

388
00:26:42.743 --> 00:26:44.828
That's what makes us different
than the others.

389
00:26:44.912 --> 00:26:46.121
I'm not a soldier.

390
00:26:47.998 --> 00:26:49.208
I come to win.

391
00:26:50.083 --> 00:26:51.793
[item clatters]

392
00:26:51.877 --> 00:26:53.086
Mmm.

393
00:27:14.441 --> 00:27:16.109
- Your Majesty.
- Captain.

394
00:27:16.193 --> 00:27:17.861
The heralds are ready to announce you.

395
00:27:17.945 --> 00:27:19.112
Thank you.

396
00:27:19.196 --> 00:27:21.865
[breathes heavily]

397
00:27:21.949 --> 00:27:24.284
How do I send people
off to a war I didn't start?

398
00:27:25.953 --> 00:27:28.455
- Are you asking my advice?
- Yes.

399
00:27:28.539 --> 00:27:29.957
Excellent.

400
00:27:30.040 --> 00:27:32.167
I have none to give.
but thank you for asking.

401
00:27:36.004 --> 00:27:37.422
- Listen to me.
- [inhales sharply]

402
00:27:38.882 --> 00:27:40.968
This is the role you were born for.

403
00:27:42.636 --> 00:27:45.138
I don't doubt for an instant
you'll find the words.

404
00:27:47.558 --> 00:27:49.268
- Harlan.
- The queen is ready.

405
00:27:50.143 --> 00:27:51.353
Yes. sir.

406
00:28:02.364 --> 00:28:04.825
[horn blowing]

407
00:28:04.908 --> 00:28:06.451
[man] Her Majesty the queen.

408
00:28:08.078 --> 00:28:09.746
[bells jingling]

409
00:28:17.045 --> 00:28:18.046
Charlotte.

410
00:28:19.756 --> 00:28:22.009
You didn't think
I'd let you sneak off again. did you?

411
00:28:22.092 --> 00:28:24.553
I thought the Compass stayed out
of war and politics.

412
00:28:24.636 --> 00:28:25.679
We do.

413
00:28:25.762 --> 00:28:28.056
My only charge. though.
is to bring you back alive.

414
00:28:28.140 --> 00:28:31.143
And if that means killing a whole mess
of Trivantian soldiers. so be it.

415
00:28:31.226 --> 00:28:32.769
- Hey. Kofun.
- Haniwa.

416
00:29:01.298 --> 00:29:03.091
[bells jingling]

417
00:29:09.348 --> 00:29:11.016
Citizens of Paya.

418
00:29:17.648 --> 00:29:21.109
My sister has put our nation
in great jeopardy.

419
00:29:22.986 --> 00:29:25.948
It was because of
her manipulation and lies

420
00:29:26.657 --> 00:29:30.953
that we now face the Trivantian army
at our doorstep.

421
00:29:32.871 --> 00:29:34.373
I won't deny this.

422
00:29:35.374 --> 00:29:36.875
You've been lied to enough.

423
00:29:38.377 --> 00:29:41.088
From this queen.
you will only hear the truth.

424
00:29:44.967 --> 00:29:46.426
And the truth is…

425
00:29:48.136 --> 00:29:51.139
we face an enemy
more powerful than we are.

426
00:29:52.349 --> 00:29:53.767
They have more men.

427
00:29:54.518 --> 00:29:57.020
They are better armed and better trained.

428
00:29:58.438 --> 00:30:00.190
So if you are afraid…

429
00:30:01.650 --> 00:30:03.443
know that you are not alone.

430
00:30:06.655 --> 00:30:09.741
Unlike my sister. I am a mother and wife.

431
00:30:11.618 --> 00:30:13.245
And I am terrified.

432
00:30:15.622 --> 00:30:19.293
For many years. I made my home
in the mountains with the Alkenny.

433
00:30:19.376 --> 00:30:23.881
where we cherished nothing
above family and community.

434
00:30:23.964 --> 00:30:26.466
and where every life was precious.

435
00:30:28.177 --> 00:30:31.054
And I address you now. not as your queen.

436
00:30:31.638 --> 00:30:35.017
but as a mother and a wife.

437
00:30:36.310 --> 00:30:39.313
And I address you. not as warriors.

438
00:30:39.396 --> 00:30:43.692
but husbands and wives.
and sons and daughters.

439
00:30:43.775 --> 00:30:45.569
We are all scared.

440
00:30:46.236 --> 00:30:48.572
And we all have so much to lose.

441
00:30:50.324 --> 00:30:51.992
So at this moment…

442
00:30:53.410 --> 00:30:55.245
I offer you this comfort.

443
00:30:57.456 --> 00:31:00.626
In all the generations
that Paya has struggled

444
00:31:00.709 --> 00:31:02.669
to survive Trivantian aggression…

445
00:31:04.338 --> 00:31:06.298
we have never been conquered.

446
00:31:06.840 --> 00:31:12.262
Trivantian boots have never walked
on this soil. and they never will!

447
00:31:12.346 --> 00:31:15.432
[warriors cheering]

448
00:31:16.308 --> 00:31:20.395
No amount of God bone or fire
will ever be enough

449
00:31:20.479 --> 00:31:22.648
to separate us from this land.

450
00:31:22.731 --> 00:31:26.944
the land of our families.
the land of our ancestors!

451
00:31:27.027 --> 00:31:28.904
[warriors cheering]

452
00:31:33.075 --> 00:31:37.371
I believe in a future
far better than our past.

453
00:31:37.454 --> 00:31:41.375
One where we and our families
will thrive and prosper

454
00:31:41.458 --> 00:31:45.629
in a land safe from hate and bigotry.

455
00:31:45.712 --> 00:31:48.382
and safe from invading armies.

456
00:31:48.465 --> 00:31:52.094
And it is that future we fight for today.

457
00:31:54.137 --> 00:31:55.806
So. my fellow Payans…

458
00:31:57.140 --> 00:32:01.103
brave sons and daughters of Paya…

459
00:32:02.855 --> 00:32:04.106
be swift.

460
00:32:05.315 --> 00:32:06.817
Be strong.

461
00:32:07.776 --> 00:32:09.444
And let the enemy know

462
00:32:09.528 --> 00:32:12.948
that their blood may fall on our land.

463
00:32:13.031 --> 00:32:17.286
but it will remain. now and forever.

464
00:32:17.369 --> 00:32:20.080
Payan land!

465
00:32:20.163 --> 00:32:22.166
[warriors cheering]

466
00:32:29.548 --> 00:32:31.550
[cheering continues]

467
00:32:37.681 --> 00:32:40.559
[horn blowing]

468
00:32:40.642 --> 00:32:42.644
- Tak!
- [warriors] Tak!

469
00:32:48.483 --> 00:32:49.484
Paris.

470
00:32:49.568 --> 00:32:52.571
Here. Baba Voss. at your side.

471
00:32:54.573 --> 00:32:56.742
You will face Edo again.

472
00:32:58.702 --> 00:33:00.412
I cannot kill my own brother.

473
00:33:00.495 --> 00:33:01.914
Then he will kill you.

474
00:33:02.873 --> 00:33:04.374
Maybe.

475
00:33:04.458 --> 00:33:06.376
And you think then you'll be absolved?

476
00:33:07.044 --> 00:33:08.962
Use your mind. lump.

477
00:33:10.088 --> 00:33:13.467
Think of your children.
Who will protect them from him?

478
00:33:14.718 --> 00:33:17.221
- You will.
- Oh. don't be daft. Baba.

479
00:33:19.389 --> 00:33:20.974
I've never thanked you.

480
00:33:21.058 --> 00:33:22.059
For what?

481
00:33:23.852 --> 00:33:25.354
Everything.

482
00:33:25.437 --> 00:33:26.855
- [breathes heavily]
- All of it.

483
00:33:27.898 --> 00:33:31.401
You bring your children back to me safely.
and it's settled.

484
00:33:33.695 --> 00:33:34.696
Yes.

485
00:33:37.157 --> 00:33:39.034
But I need you to do something for me.

486
00:33:51.672 --> 00:33:52.756
[Haniwa] Mama.

487
00:33:53.674 --> 00:33:55.592
[sighs] My children.

488
00:33:59.555 --> 00:34:02.015
I wish I could convince you
to stay here with me.

489
00:34:02.975 --> 00:34:06.478
What kind of princess and prince
would we be if we hid from the war?

490
00:34:07.396 --> 00:34:09.147
I chose this. You didn't.

491
00:34:09.231 --> 00:34:10.440
We choose it now.

492
00:34:20.284 --> 00:34:23.203
Take care of each other. Hmm?

493
00:34:23.287 --> 00:34:24.580
- We will.
- We will.

494
00:34:24.663 --> 00:34:25.831
We promise.

495
00:34:26.874 --> 00:34:27.875
Go on.

496
00:34:30.002 --> 00:34:31.336
[sniffles]

497
00:34:32.462 --> 00:34:33.463
Maghra.

498
00:34:36.008 --> 00:34:38.719
Baba. [sniffles]

499
00:34:40.012 --> 00:34:41.388
Come back to me.

500
00:34:42.472 --> 00:34:43.765
With our family.

501
00:34:49.605 --> 00:34:50.647
Yes.

502
00:35:26.725 --> 00:35:28.142
[breathes shakily]

503
00:35:37.361 --> 00:35:38.611
[Paris] Toad!

504
00:35:38.695 --> 00:35:39.905
[Toad] Here. Paris.

505
00:35:43.575 --> 00:35:45.160
I heard they had you on home defense.

506
00:35:46.453 --> 00:35:49.915
[sighs] A soldier of my rank and skill
building barricades.

507
00:35:49.997 --> 00:35:51.457
I should be on the front lines.

508
00:35:51.542 --> 00:35:53.752
[scoffs]
If I had known you'd take it so hard.

509
00:35:53.836 --> 00:35:56.463
I would've thought twice
before asking the queen to arrange it.

510
00:35:58.881 --> 00:36:00.133
What are you talking about?

511
00:36:00.217 --> 00:36:03.720
I have to take a trip.
I thought you might want to come with me.

512
00:36:05.430 --> 00:36:06.515
Where are we going?

513
00:36:06.598 --> 00:36:08.517
I'll explain on the way.

514
00:36:08.600 --> 00:36:09.810
Prepare a horse for me.

515
00:36:10.394 --> 00:36:12.271
A good horse. Your horse!

516
00:36:12.938 --> 00:36:14.231
We leave at once.

517
00:36:39.047 --> 00:36:40.257
It's an airplane.

518
00:36:41.550 --> 00:36:42.551
Yeah.

519
00:36:44.553 --> 00:36:48.182
Must have been so terrifying.
falling out of the sky in a metal tube.

520
00:36:49.892 --> 00:36:52.978
Almost like they had no business
being up there in the first place.

521
00:37:09.912 --> 00:37:12.664
[Paris] This saddle is not soft.

522
00:37:12.748 --> 00:37:14.958
- [Toad sighs]
- Did you ever hear of oiling a saddle?

523
00:37:16.335 --> 00:37:20.172
[Toad] Sometimes a simple "thank you"
is all you have to say.

524
00:37:20.756 --> 00:37:23.717
[Paris chuckles] You're in a mood.

525
00:37:24.885 --> 00:37:28.013
I'm used to marching toward the fight.
not away from it.

526
00:37:29.014 --> 00:37:33.185
This war is gonna be so much bigger
than one battle.

527
00:37:33.268 --> 00:37:34.770
Not if we lose this one.

528
00:37:35.395 --> 00:37:37.773
This war is not about Trivantes and Paya.

529
00:37:39.650 --> 00:37:42.194
The world is about to change. Toad.

530
00:37:42.277 --> 00:37:43.862
Sight is returning.

531
00:37:44.988 --> 00:37:46.615
That's what this war is about.

532
00:37:47.658 --> 00:37:50.285
even if those who wage it are unaware.

533
00:37:50.994 --> 00:37:52.246
What I'm aware of is that

534
00:37:52.329 --> 00:37:56.041
our new queen is asking us
not only to forget our beliefs.

535
00:37:56.917 --> 00:37:58.544
but to go to war against them.

536
00:37:58.627 --> 00:38:01.088
Maghra is much more than a Kane.

537
00:38:01.839 --> 00:38:06.844
She is Haniwa and Kofun's mother.
They hold the keys to our future.

538
00:38:07.928 --> 00:38:09.763
[Toad] Have you dreamed that future?

539
00:38:10.681 --> 00:38:13.809
I dream multiple futures. Oh. oh.

540
00:38:16.687 --> 00:38:18.397
And on what do they depend?

541
00:38:19.439 --> 00:38:24.111
They depend on small things like
you and me making this journey safely.

542
00:38:27.614 --> 00:38:29.324
None of this makes any sense.

543
00:38:30.909 --> 00:38:32.160
Then why did you come?

544
00:38:35.455 --> 00:38:36.748
Because you asked me to.

545
00:38:37.374 --> 00:38:40.294
[chimes clinking]

546
00:38:40.377 --> 00:38:42.004
[Paris] We camp here for the night.

547
00:38:43.005 --> 00:38:45.233
[Toad] God Flame is still strong.
We should press further.

548
00:38:45.257 --> 00:38:47.176
[Paris] No. I have my reasons.

549
00:38:48.010 --> 00:38:49.636
This is the spot.

550
00:39:11.491 --> 00:39:13.243
[Toad] You should sleep here with me.

551
00:39:24.755 --> 00:39:26.048
What did you say?

552
00:39:26.131 --> 00:39:29.384
[sighs]

553
00:39:29.468 --> 00:39:31.678
We'll be warmer if we sleep together.

554
00:39:35.682 --> 00:39:36.892
[sighs]

555
00:39:38.435 --> 00:39:39.478
[grunts]

556
00:39:41.021 --> 00:39:43.273
[sighs] Point well taken. soldier.

557
00:39:45.442 --> 00:39:47.903
[chuckles] Oh.

558
00:39:47.986 --> 00:39:49.154
Mmm.

559
00:39:50.113 --> 00:39:52.783
- [grunts]
- [sighs] I'll be a perfect gentleman.

560
00:39:52.866 --> 00:39:55.077
[sighs]

561
00:39:56.370 --> 00:40:00.958
If I thought that were true.
I wouldn't bother coming over here.

562
00:40:02.543 --> 00:40:04.461
- [sighs]
- [moans]

563
00:40:04.545 --> 00:40:05.754
[kisses]

564
00:40:07.339 --> 00:40:09.341
[Paris moans]

565
00:40:11.134 --> 00:40:14.137
[chimes clinking]

566
00:40:14.221 --> 00:40:15.597
Someone's out there.

567
00:40:17.349 --> 00:40:18.767
[grunts. gasps]

568
00:40:33.282 --> 00:40:34.908
What's troubling you. Kofun?

569
00:40:37.661 --> 00:40:41.248
Besides going into battle with
the most powerful army on the continent?

570
00:40:41.790 --> 00:40:43.292
Yes. aside from that.

571
00:40:46.336 --> 00:40:47.462
Nothing. I'm fine.

572
00:40:47.546 --> 00:40:51.592
Come on. You've barely said a word
since I got back from the peace summit.

573
00:40:54.136 --> 00:40:55.762
It's been kind of a busy time.

574
00:40:56.930 --> 00:40:58.432
Our mother is the queen.

575
00:40:59.266 --> 00:41:02.311
You're a prince. I'm a princess…

576
00:41:04.021 --> 00:41:06.440
We're going to war.
and you have nothing to say?

577
00:41:10.777 --> 00:41:11.945
What are you reading?

578
00:41:14.573 --> 00:41:17.784
[sighs] It's a book of poems.
I found it in Trivantes.

579
00:41:19.119 --> 00:41:20.621
There were books in Trivantes?

580
00:41:21.288 --> 00:41:23.373
There were lots of surprises in Trivantes.

581
00:41:26.960 --> 00:41:28.712
Will you read something to me?

582
00:41:28.795 --> 00:41:30.005
Read it yourself.

583
00:41:31.256 --> 00:41:32.382
Please?

584
00:41:38.931 --> 00:41:45.562
"Turning and turning in the widening gyre
The falcon cannot hear the falconer;

585
00:41:47.689 --> 00:41:52.194
<i>Things fall apart; the center cannot hold;</i>

586
00:41:54.112 --> 00:41:56.990
<i>Mere anarchy is loosed upon the world.</i>

587
00:41:58.909 --> 00:42:01.662
<i>The blood-dimmed tide is loosed…</i>

588
00:42:01.745 --> 00:42:03.539
[metal clangs]

589
00:42:03.622 --> 00:42:04.957
<i>…and everywhere</i>

590
00:42:05.040 --> 00:42:07.793
<i>The ceremony of innocence is drowned;</i>

591
00:42:10.212 --> 00:42:14.091
<i>The best lack all conviction.
while the worst</i>

592
00:42:14.174 --> 00:42:16.802
<i>Are full of passionate intensity.</i>

593
00:42:20.222 --> 00:42:22.975
<i>Surely some revelation is at hand;</i>

594
00:42:23.892 --> 00:42:26.937
<i>Surely the Second Coming is at hand.</i>

595
00:42:27.771 --> 00:42:29.106
<i>The Second Coming!</i>

596
00:42:31.483 --> 00:42:33.318
<i>Hardly are those words out</i>

597
00:42:33.402 --> 00:42:37.573
<i>When a vast image out of</i> Spiritus Mundi
<i>Troubles my sight:</i>

598
00:42:39.241 --> 00:42:41.910
somewhere in the sands of the desert

599
00:42:41.994 --> 00:42:45.289
A shape with lion body
and the head of a man.

600
00:42:46.165 --> 00:42:49.668
A gaze blank and pitiless as the sun.

601
00:42:49.751 --> 00:42:53.338
Is moving its slow thighs.
while all about it

602
00:42:53.422 --> 00:42:56.049
Reel shadows
of the indignant desert birds.

603
00:42:57.843 --> 00:43:01.263
<i>The darkness drops again; but now I know</i>

604
00:43:01.346 --> 00:43:04.516
<i>That twenty centuries of stony sleep</i>

605
00:43:04.600 --> 00:43:08.520
<i>Were vexed to nightmare
by a rocking cradle.</i>

606
00:43:11.899 --> 00:43:14.234
<i>And what rough beast.</i>

607
00:43:14.318 --> 00:43:16.236
<i>its hour come round at last.</i>

608
00:43:16.862 --> 00:43:20.532
<i>Slouches towards Bethlehem to be born?"</i>

609
00:43:29.208 --> 00:43:30.417
[grunts]

610
00:43:39.218 --> 00:43:40.219
[safe opens]

611
00:44:35.649 --> 00:44:37.234
- [shouts]
- [weapon whistling]

612
00:44:37.317 --> 00:44:39.778
[grunting]

613
00:44:46.034 --> 00:44:47.870
[both grunting]

614
00:44:56.086 --> 00:44:57.421
[Maghra grunts]

615
00:44:57.504 --> 00:44:58.630
[coughing]

616
00:45:01.258 --> 00:45:03.844
[coughing. grunting]

617
00:45:03.927 --> 00:45:05.429
- Maghra. run!
- Harlan!

618
00:45:05.971 --> 00:45:07.973
[pants]

619
00:45:08.473 --> 00:45:10.642
- [assassin grunts]
- [Maghra] Harlan!

620
00:45:11.268 --> 00:45:12.436
[Harlan shouts]

621
00:45:17.941 --> 00:45:19.484
Trivantian fuckers!

622
00:45:19.568 --> 00:45:21.403
[grunting]

623
00:45:24.406 --> 00:45:27.409
- [assassin shouts]
- [grunting]

624
00:45:32.956 --> 00:45:34.958
- [grunts]
- [screams]

625
00:45:35.792 --> 00:45:37.419
[Maghra shouts]

626
00:45:42.007 --> 00:45:44.009
[grunting]

627
00:45:48.680 --> 00:45:51.308
[chokes. shouting]

628
00:45:55.812 --> 00:45:58.273
[screams]

629
00:45:58.357 --> 00:45:59.441
[grunts]

630
00:45:59.525 --> 00:46:02.361
[coughing. gasping]

631
00:46:05.739 --> 00:46:07.115
Harlan?

632
00:46:07.199 --> 00:46:09.243
- [coughs]
- [Harlan] Maghra. Oh.

633
00:46:10.452 --> 00:46:12.704
I'm so pleased I stayed to protect you.

634
00:46:12.788 --> 00:46:14.331
Where are you hurt?

635
00:46:14.414 --> 00:46:16.208
- Pretty much everywhere.
- [groans]

636
00:46:16.291 --> 00:46:18.252
- Are there more of them?
- I don't think so.

637
00:46:18.335 --> 00:46:19.753
- [groans]
- Guards!

638
00:46:20.838 --> 00:46:22.381
No. stay with me.

639
00:46:22.464 --> 00:46:24.258
- [laughs]
- [panting]

640
00:46:24.341 --> 00:46:26.927
I thought you'd never ask. [chuckles]

641
00:46:27.010 --> 00:46:28.011
[sighs]

642
00:46:47.489 --> 00:46:51.034
We made it here before the Trivantians.
Make base!

643
00:47:01.336 --> 00:47:03.589
We're now at 160 fighters.

644
00:47:03.672 --> 00:47:06.425
We picked up another ten recruits
from towns along the way.

645
00:47:08.093 --> 00:47:10.888
If the Trivantians are indeed 250 strong…

646
00:47:11.763 --> 00:47:14.933
This fort was designed to eliminate
any advantage of numbers.

647
00:47:15.017 --> 00:47:18.312
The narrow trenches will squeeze
the Trivantians

648
00:47:18.395 --> 00:47:19.980
and equalize the battlefield.

649
00:47:21.231 --> 00:47:22.983
Have you fought here before?

650
00:47:24.526 --> 00:47:25.527
Never.

651
00:47:43.754 --> 00:47:44.838
They're here.

652
00:47:45.839 --> 00:47:47.007
[whispers] Papa.

653
00:48:13.575 --> 00:48:16.119
- [man shouts]
- [soldiers shouting]

654
00:48:30.133 --> 00:48:31.552
There's too many of them.

655
00:48:32.594 --> 00:48:33.804
Ayura.

656
00:48:40.978 --> 00:48:43.480
I count close to 350. sir.

657
00:48:46.358 --> 00:48:47.693
[sighs]

658
00:48:47.776 --> 00:48:50.195
Gosset's spies were wrong.

659
00:49:13.010 --> 00:49:14.094
They're here.

660
00:49:15.596 --> 00:49:17.222
Earlier than we anticipated.

661
00:49:17.890 --> 00:49:20.642
It won't matter. Who do you see?

662
00:49:22.269 --> 00:49:24.188
About a hundred soldiers
in front of the gate.

663
00:49:24.271 --> 00:49:26.064
There'll be more inside the fort.

664
00:49:26.148 --> 00:49:27.149
Captain…

665
00:49:28.317 --> 00:49:30.068
I did not ask what you see.

666
00:49:30.152 --> 00:49:33.405
I asked. "Who do you see?"

667
00:49:39.328 --> 00:49:40.704
I see Baba Voss.

668
00:49:41.663 --> 00:49:42.664
[Edo Voss] Good.

669
00:49:44.124 --> 00:49:45.768
[Tamacti Jun]
We fight them in the trenches.

670
00:49:45.792 --> 00:49:47.270
That's where we'll have the advantage.

671
00:49:47.294 --> 00:49:49.796
- [man] Drummers!
- [drums beating]

672
00:49:50.422 --> 00:49:51.715
Will it be enough?

673
00:49:51.798 --> 00:49:52.841
[Tamacti Jun] No.

674
00:49:52.925 --> 00:49:56.053
But at least we'll kill many more of them
before we're overrun.

675
00:49:59.264 --> 00:50:01.099
- No.
- What are you doing?

676
00:50:01.183 --> 00:50:02.392
Charlotte.

677
00:50:02.476 --> 00:50:03.644
Someone has to stop this.

678
00:50:04.269 --> 00:50:07.481
- What are you talking about?
- I have a friend on the other side.

679
00:50:07.564 --> 00:50:10.084
If I can get to them and tell them
the queen has been deposed...

680
00:50:10.108 --> 00:50:13.028
- Haniwa. they will kill you.
- You have to trust me.

681
00:50:13.111 --> 00:50:15.280
[breathes shakily]

682
00:50:15.364 --> 00:50:16.365
[grunts]

683
00:50:18.367 --> 00:50:19.368
Papa.

684
00:50:24.081 --> 00:50:25.999
[sighs]

685
00:50:26.083 --> 00:50:27.209
Let her go.

686
00:50:27.292 --> 00:50:28.335
[Kofun] What?

687
00:50:29.628 --> 00:50:31.255
We're out of choices. my boy.

688
00:50:32.714 --> 00:50:33.799
Let her try.

689
00:50:58.991 --> 00:51:01.368
[panting]

690
00:51:02.286 --> 00:51:05.006
- [Wren] You shouldn't be here.
- [Haniwa] None of us should be here.

691
00:51:07.958 --> 00:51:10.627
What you did at the peace conference…

692
00:51:10.711 --> 00:51:12.629
It was Queen Kane
who attacked your people.

693
00:51:13.213 --> 00:51:17.634
She would do anything for her holy war.
You need to know that it wasn't us.

694
00:51:18.927 --> 00:51:21.680
Wren. I would die before I hurt you.
You have to believe that.

695
00:51:27.269 --> 00:51:28.645
I do believe you.

696
00:51:31.565 --> 00:51:33.650
The queen is no longer in power.

697
00:51:33.734 --> 00:51:35.736
My mother took the throne
as soon as we got back.

698
00:51:36.570 --> 00:51:37.696
Maghra's the queen?

699
00:51:37.779 --> 00:51:40.240
Yes. And she does not want this war.

700
00:51:40.324 --> 00:51:42.034
You could talk to Edo.

701
00:51:44.077 --> 00:51:45.579
No. he won't listen to me.

702
00:51:45.662 --> 00:51:47.331
You have to try.

703
00:51:48.916 --> 00:51:51.585
Hundreds of Trivantians and Payans
will die for a lie

704
00:51:51.668 --> 00:51:54.630
- if we don't stop this right now.
- [drumming]

705
00:51:57.049 --> 00:51:59.843
It's too late. You have to go back.

706
00:51:59.927 --> 00:52:01.011
What?

707
00:52:04.097 --> 00:52:05.974
- Wren.
- [man] Archers!

708
00:52:06.058 --> 00:52:07.100
[gasps]

709
00:52:08.143 --> 00:52:09.144
Run.

710
00:52:09.895 --> 00:52:11.313
[man] Arrows up!

711
00:52:12.731 --> 00:52:13.899
Fire!

712
00:52:13.982 --> 00:52:16.068
[panting]

713
00:52:16.092 --> 00:52:18.092
